---

import GradientBorder from "./elements/GradientBorder.astro";---
<section class="fit-section">
  <h2>Are <span class="gradient-text">we</span> a fit?</h2>
  <div class="fit-section__content">
    <div class="fit-section__item">
      <h3>We’re a good fit if:</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>You’re a founder or product owner who cares about quality, not just the pitch deck</li>
        <li>You want one senior partner actually doing the work, not a rotating cast of juniors</li>
        <li>You have a real problem to solve (revenue, efficiency, UX), not just “we should do something with AI”</li>
        <li>You’re okay with honest feedback on scope, timeline, and trade-offs</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <GradientBorder class="fit-section__item not-fit">
      <h3>We’re not a fit if:</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>You want the cheapest quote</li>
        <li>You’re looking for a pure “hands-off, we’ll figure out what we want later” engagement</li>
        <li>You’re not sure about the requirements and what you want to achieve</li>
      </ul>
    </GradientBorder>
  </div>
</section>

<style lang="scss">
.fit-section {
  text-align: center;
  padding: 2rem 0 4rem;

  h2 {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  &__content {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    align-items: stretch;
    justify-content: center;
    text-align: left;

    @media (min-width: 768px) {
      flex-direction: row;
    }
  }

  &__item {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--accent-color), var(--accent-dark));
    color: var(--background-light);
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 1rem;
    flex: 1 1 50%;

    &.not-fit {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--background-light), var(--background-darker));
      color: var(--text-color)
    }

    h3 {
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      font-size: 1.875rem;;
    }

    ul {
      list-style-type: square;
      padding-left: 1.5rem;
      margin: 0;

      li {
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
        padding-left: 0.5rem;

        @media (min-width: 768px) {
          font-size: 1.15rem;
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
</style>